The paper deals with location privacy preservation, which is a topic closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves synthesizing artificial traces, which requires techniques from database management (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of semantic models, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and potentially social networks (cs.SI) if the semantic features are related to social interactions.
